  "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/issues/1430",
  "title": "instantsearch.js and AMD (requirejs & almond)",
  "body": "Does instantsearch provide support for AMD?\n\nThe reason I am asking this is that in my implementation using requirejs and almond, I am getting the following error from Almond: `Uncaught Error: See almond README: incorrect module build, no module name`\n[Here is an explanation of it.](https://github.com/requirejs/almond/blob/master/README.md#incorrect-module-build-no-module-name)\n\nIn the instantsearch.js code, the module is defined here:\n\n```\nif(typeof exports === 'object' && typeof module === 'object')\n        module.exports = factory();\n    else if(typeof define === 'function' && define.amd)\n        define([], factory);\n    else if(typeof exports === 'object')\n        exports[\"instantsearch\"] = factory();\n    else\n        root[\"instantsearch\"] = factory();\n```\n\nIf I modify this and give `define([], factory);` a name like `define('instantsearch', [], factory);` then everything is fine.\n\nHas anyone had success implementing instantsearch using Almond.js?\n",
  "created_at": "2016-10-17T21:41:24Z",
